items.title: The organic route to energy security
items.description: Ethanol blended petrol in India is here to stay, with the proportion of ethanol reaching 14.6 percent in 2023-24. Government estimates that a decade of ethanol blended petrol has resulted in a savings of over Rs 1 lakh crore. The initial results show that doubling down on biofuels will not only lower energy import dependence but help the country meet its climate obligations
